==== beat-1
================================================================
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
 BEAT 1 — MEASURE THE PRIOR PERIOD  (pulse, seeded + deterministic)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
 TALKING POINT:
   Before Como prescribes anything, we measure. pulse collects the team's
   sentiment with cryptographic anonymity — k-anonymity suppression is
   tested on both sides of the threshold, so nobody's answer is ever
   identifiable. The demo runs the seeded simulation: same seed, byte-for-
   byte identical report. Determinism is designed in, not hoped for —
   watch us prove it by running it twice.

kit: pulse -> ../pulse (sibling checkout)
 RUN: just dogfood   (in the pulse repo — twice, to prove determinism)

