================================================================
==== beat-5
================================================================
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
 BEAT 5 — MEASURE  (tuesday --strict + the Adopt<->Measure cross-check)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
 TALKING POINT:
   Adoption you can count, not activity you take on faith. tuesday reads the
   merged PRs off the client's forge and rolls measured hours up per
   decision — strict mode exits nonzero if even one merged PR is
   unaccounted for. Then the double-entry bookkeeping: conduit's verify and
   tuesday's report are two independent codebases, and the cross-check
   asserts they agree on the same PR, the same effort label, the same
   decision. Finally, the loop closes: this report plus the pulse signal
   feed the next assessment — which is where this demo began.

kit: tuesday -> ../tuesday (sibling checkout)
 RUN: tuesday-report --source gitea --owner como --repo playbook --monthly-hours 160 -o json --strict
      (= tuesday's own `just dogfood-report playbook`; token rides the env, never argv or git)
   exit code: 0 (strict mode satisfied)

 EVIDENCE — decision-attributed effort (the Measure artifact):
   como 2026-June: 1 allocation(s), 0 unallocated PR(s) [strict requires 0]
   PR 2 "[ADR-0005] Automated Testing" -> ADR-0005 (SuperQuick, 160.0h)
   adr_totals: ADR-0005 = 160.0h

 RUN: cross-check (Adopt vs Measure — two codebases, one ground truth)
   pr:     conduit=2 tuesday=2
   effort: conduit=effort:1-super-quick tuesday=effort:1-super-quick (SuperQuick)
   adr:    conduit=ADR-0005 tuesday=ADR-0005 (adr_totals: 160.0h)
   CROSS-CHECK PASS: PR 2, effort:1-super-quick, ADR-0005 — Adopt and Measure agree

 EVIDENCE — the closed loop:
   next-period inputs ready: /home/brett/repos/como-tech/conduit/demo/runs/kit-20260612T153221Z/tuesday-report.json + /home/brett/repos/como-tech/conduit/demo/runs/kit-20260612T153221Z/pulse-report.json
